verbose_text: Overall, it is suggested that the downregulation of surface MHC class I molecules and IFN- gammaR1 by K3- and K5 mediated ubiquitination and lysosomal degradation inhibits primary host immunity against viral infection.
evidence: MHC class I molecules and IFN- gammaR1 by K3- and K5-mediated ubiquitination and lysosomal degradation inhibits primary host immunity
